title: PANCAKES
ingredients: ['2 cups Bisquick', '1 egg', '1 ⅔ cups milk']
instructions: Beat the ingredients (2 cups Bisquick, 1 egg, 1 ⅔ cups milk) with a rotary beater until well blended. Pour batter onto a heated griddle. Turn pancakes when bubbles appear.
notes: _Makes about 18 4" pancakes._ For thinner pancakes use 2 cups milk.

title: MUFFINS
instructions: Heat oven to 400° (mod. hot). Blend together the ingredients.

title: BISQUICK MUFFINS
instructions: Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. (For richer batter, add 2 tbsp. more sugar, 2 tbsp. melted shortening or salad oil.) Fill 12 well greased muffin cups ⅔ full. Bake for 15 min.
notes: _For richer batter_, add 2 tbsp. more sugar, 2 tbsp. melted shortening or salad oil.

title: WAFFLES
ingredients: ['2 cups Bisquick', '1 ⅔ cups milk', '1 egg', '2 tbsp. salad oil or melted shortening']
instructions: Beat the ingredients with a rotary beater until well blended. Spoon onto hot waffle baker.

title: COFFEE CAKE
ingredients: ['Muffin batter', '2 tsp. cinnamon', '¼ cup sugar', '2 tbsp. Bisquick', '2 tbsp. soft butter']
instructions: Make Muffin batter. Spread into greased 9" round layer pan or 8 or 9" square pan. Sprinkle with mixture of: 2 tsp. cinnamon, ¼ cup sugar, 2 tbsp. Bisquick, 2 tbsp. soft butter. Blend with fork until crumbly. Bake _20 to 25 min._

title: DUMPLINGS
instructions: Mix 2 cups Bisquick, ¾ cup milk well with a fork. Drop tablespoonfuls gently onto boiling stew. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, uncovered and for 10 minutes covered. Let the stew bubble gently.

title: GOOD BISCUITS
instructions: ['Add ⅔ cup milk _all at once_ to 2 cups Bisquick. Stir with fork into a soft dough.', 'Beat dough 15 strokes.', 'Roll dough around on cloth-covered board lightly dusted with Bisquick to prevent sticking.']
